.help ckcal March2012 gemini.gemtools
.ih
NAME
ckcal -- Check lamp and sdist calibration files and return an updated list
.ih
USAGE
ckcal 
.ih
PARAMETERS
.ls lampfiles = "" 
List of input wavelength calibration files. The list may be given as a  
comma  separated  list, a @filelist, or using wildcards. The number of 
lampfiles must either be equal to one or equal to the number of input 
NIFS spectra.
.le
.ls sdistfiles = ""
List of input S-distortion calibration files containing @file names or image 
templates. The list may be given as a comma separated  list, a @filelist, 
or using wildcards. The number of calibration files must either be equal to 
one or equal to the number of input spectra.
.le
.ls outlist = ""
List to update with input lamp files and S-distortion files.
.le
.ls nfiles = 0
Number of files in input list. \fInfiles\fR is CKINPUT output.
.le
.ls nver = 0
Number of extensions. \fInver\fR is CKINPUT output.
.le
.ls sci_ext = "SCI"
Name of the MEF extension containing the science data.
.le
.ls database = ""
Location of lampfiles and sdistfiles.
.le
.ls name = "CKCAL"
Name of task calling CKCAL for use in \fIlogfile\fR.
.le
.ls logfile = "STDOUT"
Name of the logfile containing error and warning messages. 
.le
.ls verbose = yes
Print actions to the screen and logfile.
.le
.ls vverbose = no
Print every action to the screen.
.le

RETURN VALUES
.ls nlamps (output)
Number of lamp files
.le
.ls nsdist (output)
Number of S-distortion calibration files
.le
.ls status = 0
Exit status will be non-zero if CKCAL halted with an error.  This 
parameter is always set by the task and should not be modified by the user.
.le
.ih
DESCRIPTION
CKCAL verifies that lamp wavelength calibration files and S-distortion files
exist and adds them to an output list. Because it adds to the existing outlist,
CKCAL is usually called after CKINPUT.

CKCAL is not meant to be a stand-alone task used from a command line prompt.

.ih
EXAMPLES
1. Verify calibration files exist in database. Append calibration files to
tmpin for processing in NSFITCOORDS.  
.sp
.nf
    ni> ckcal (lampfiles=lamptransf, sdistfiles=sdisttransf,
    >>> outlist=tmpin, nfiles=nfiles, nver=nver, sci_ext=l_sci_ext,
    >>> database=s_database, name="NSFITCOORDS", logfile=l_logfile,
    >>> verbose=l_verbose, vverbose=no)
.fi
.ih
BUGS AND LIMITATIONS
.ih
SEE ALSO
ckinput, nsfitcoords
.endhelp
